"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity.md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity.md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity.md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity.md#Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity. Adding certain switches can induce apoptosis or cytotoxicity. Gene editing can also introduce targetable effectors and antigens where a drug can act as the switch. These are so called 'suicide genes' such as RQR8 and HSV-TK Mut 2. [[Pharmaceutical switches, such as dasatinib, to temporarily halt CAR-T activation are fast activators to avoid over-activation of the immune system.]]{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity.md#References":true},"mtime":1709479601284,"size":661,"hash":"5a0f9c24ac79cbee051254cb5174def15a5c85f226569342ee305cc72fb5206c"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00655552,0.00379781,-0.02495705,0.03849605,0.03955773,-0.00164824,-0.004582,-0.02776736,-0.01276955,0.00643276,-0.00617531,-0.00185506,-0.0384974,-0.05258342,0.02055122,-0.00008291,0.04057164,-0.01353959,0.02627785,-0.00763468,0.11168553,-0.0085923,-0.00843165,0.02709448,-0.05500269,-0.02219933,0.0088019,0.00197841,-0.0667905,-0.06233766,0.00012839,0.01638713,0.0298526,0.01874141,0.01678123,0.00497814,0.01671256,-0.0218301,0.01065632,-0.03109536,-0.02916988,-0.0014722,0.00591896,-0.00593928,0.01893472,0.04691174,0.02762124,0.00663439,0.00585579,0.03978558,-0.00647648,-0.00409326,-0.00273152,0.00830384,